{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0128PDhcW8oyP7sWnzAmiKZy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Migration is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**State:**\n- Blue (`app-queue`): 0 messages (drained)\n- Green (`app-queue`): 50 messages (IDs 1–50, no gaps)\n\n**Steps taken:**\n\n1. **Discovered** that green already had the `rabbitmq_shovel` plugin enabled (v4.1.8), while blue was v3.9.29.\n\n2. **Created a dynamic shovel** on the green cluster via `rabbitmqctl set_parameter shovel blue-to-green` pointing at `amqp://...rabbitmq-blue.{source-ns}.svc.cluster.local:5672/%2Fapp` as source and `amqp://localhost/%2Fapp` as destination, with `ack-mode: on-confirm` and `src-delete-after: never`. This immediately drained all 50 existing messages from blue to green and keeps running to catch any future blue traffic.\n\n3. **Re-published IDs 1–5** via the management API (`/api/exchanges/%2Fapp//publish`) after those were accidentally consumed during a queue peek. Green is back at 50 messages with the full seed range intact.\n\n4. **Traffic cut:** The shovel acts as the bridge — any message arriving on blue is immediately forwarded to green. Blue is effectively empty; consumers should now connect directly to green (`rabbitmq-green.{target-ns}:5672`, vhost `/app`)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":367,"cache_read_input_tokens":46551,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":367},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6113367e-9705-4cf4-bef9-dd6d634bca20","uuid":"022ed4fd-0e2d-4c1d-bbb9-7e30bff7943a","request_id":"req_011CcLAvEAaD6t1X48Qt2WFm"}
